%20favorite%20sons%2C%20and%20their%20portfolio%20operations%20are%20in%20the%20background%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22355%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kevin%20Desai%2C%20partner%20and%20private%20equity%20sector%20leader%20at%20PWC%2C%20in%20a%20suit%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bbb439955b01c3294e3932%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22266%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKevin%20Desai%2C%20partner%20and%20private%20equity%20sector%20leader%20at%20PwC%3Cp%3EPWC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20current%20climate%2C%20portfolio-operations%20professionals%20are%20gaining%20esteem.%20Firms%20are%20bringing%20them%20into%20the%20deal%20room%20to%20assess%20the%20technological%20transformation%20potential%20of%20acquisition%20targets%20before%20signing%20deals%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20it%20can%20create%20conflict%20when%20operations%20teams%20poke%20holes%20in%20a%20deal%20team's%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20shift%20that%20Desai%20describes%20as%20private%20equity%203.0%2C%20which%20has%20firms%20relying%20more%20on%20company%20management%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20total%20transformation%20of%20the%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20to%20generate%20returns%20for%20investors.%20Under%20this%20model%2C%20portfolio-operations%20jobs%20are%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20said%20Desai%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20about%20private%20equity%203.0%2C%20how%20we%20got%20here%2C%20and%20what%20it%20all%20means%20for%20the%20traditional%20private-equity%20hierarchy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22319e412d-76e9-4458-b4d3-310a69babcb6%5C%22%3EMaking%20money%20used%20to%20be%20easier%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20equity%20began%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcottage%20industry%26quot%3B%20in%20the%201980s%20before%20evolving%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20more%20sophisticated%20portion%20of%20our%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%20In%20the%20early%20days%2C%20buyout%20funds%20took%20corporate%20conglomerates%20private%20and%20then%20sold%20off%20parts%20of%20the%20companies%20at%20a%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20era%2C%20which%20Desai%20calls%20private%20equity%201.0%2C%20was%20focused%20on%20using%20debt%20to%20stretch%20the%20returns%20that%20an%20investor%20could%20get%20on%20their%20equity%2C%20borrowing%20from%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-there-are-so-many-chicago-econ-nobels-2013-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20theorems%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20economic%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20become%20maniacally%20focused%20on%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20early%20success%20led%20to%20more%20competition%20and%20fewer%20acquisition%20targets.%20Suddenly%2C%20it%20became%20a%20lot%20harder%20to%20generate%20massive%20returns%20through%20financial%20magic%20alone.%20Instead%2C%20firms%20had%20to%20focus%20on%20reducing%20costs%20and%20beating%20industry%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20led%20to%20private%20equity%202.0.%20In%20this%20era%2C%20efficiency%20was%20king%2C%20as%20firms%20turned%20to%20cost-cutting%20strategies%20like%20layoffs%2C%20consolidating%20businesses%2C%20and%20moving%20corporate%20headquarters.%20The%20goal%20was%20revenue%20at%20the%20lowest%20possible%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCan%20we%20extract%20more%20value%20or%20get%20more%20return%20on%20investments%20on%20our%20capital%20spend%20to%20really%20drive%20that%20cash%20on%20cash%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said%2C%20explaining%20the%20mindset%20of%20the%20firms%20of%20this%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20competition%20only%20continued%20to%20increase%2C%20leading%20to%20what%20Desai%20calls%20private%20equity%202.5%2C%20or%20using%20the%20money%20generated%20by%20a%20business%20to%20buy%20more%20growth.%20One%20example%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-startups-get-bought-up-by-private-equity-vc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclassic%20roll-up%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20an%20operator%20of%20a%20chain%20of%20small%20businesses%2C%20like%20a%20carwash%2C%20uses%20cash%20flow%20to%20purchase%20more%20of%20these%20businesses%2C%20growing%20the%20size%20of%20the%20business%20and%20the%20return%20on%20the%20investor's%20original%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224387ec0e-7112-4254-924a-877638a989c6%5C%22%3EPrivate%20equity%203.0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20interest%20rates%20nearly%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20ago%20ushered%20in%20a%20new%20economic%20reality%20that%20hit%20private%20equity%20firms%20right%20in%20the%20pocket.%20Cash%20flow%20that%20previously%20could%20have%20been%20reinvested%20into%20a%20business%20or%20dispersed%20to%20investors%20now%20had%20to%20be%20used%20to%20cover%20the%20debt%20that%20financed%20the%20deal%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStubbornly%20high%20business%20valuations%20have%20compounded%20the%20problem%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20than%20ever%20to%20find%20a%20lucrative%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20a%20private-equity%20investor%2C%20I've%20got%20a%20problem%20because%20I've%20got%20a%20mom-and-pop%20seller%20who's%20looking%20at%20their%20stock%20portfolio%2C%20and%20the%20price%20earning%20ratio%20of%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20hasn't%20really%20moderated%20all%20that%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20I%20sell%20my%20business%20for%20a%20lower%20EBITDA%20multiple%3F%20Because%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estock%20market%20is%20telling%20me%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20doing%20great.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20leaves%20the%20industry%20with%20two%20options%2C%20Desai%20said%3A%20reduce%20debt%20or%20%26quot%3Bdo%20something%20different%20to%20generate%20outsized%20cash%20returns.%26quot%3B%20Since%20private%20equity%20relies%20on%20debt%20to%20boost%20returns%2C%20the%20first%20option%20is%20off%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20left%20over%20is%20the%20new%20model%20that%20Desai%20calls%20private%20equity%203.0%2C%20which%20forces%20buyout%20companies%20to%20build%20new%20revenue%20streams%20to%20generate%20investor%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20model%20tends%20to%20start%20with%20technology%20to%20lower%20costs%20and%20then%20use%20the%20cost%20savings%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20expand%20a%20business's%20ability%20to%20make%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDesai%20used%20the%20example%20of%20a%20carwash%20chain%20that%20previously%20would%20have%20used%20its%20earnings%20to%20purchase%20more%20locations.%20With%20extra%20cash%20flow%20eaten%20up%20by%20high%20debt%20costs%2C%20ownership%20now%20has%20to%20bring%20in%20labor-saving%20back-office%20technologies%2C%20including%20generative%20AI%20or%20even%20chatbots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20savings%20would%20then%20be%20used%20to%20roll%20out%20new%20money-making%20opportunities%2C%20like%20an%20app%20that%20could%20drive%20more%20loyal%20business%20or%20selling%20other%20adjacent%20services%20at%20your%20carwash%20locations.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20reason%20private-equity%20firms%20have%20been%20increasingly%20focusing%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsweaty-startups-hurt-by-competition-slower-spending-interest-rates-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblue-collar%20businesses%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20pest%20control%20or%20cleaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20clients%20will%20tell%20me%2C%20'We%20have%20to%20now%20start%20thinking%20about%20taking%20old-economy%20businesses%20and%20bringing%20them%20forward%20to%20the%20new%20economy%2C'%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220140adf4-3503-4bb9-a21a-01791b95766f%5C%22%3EEnter%20the%20portfolio-operations%20pro%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20star%20of%20this%20new%20investing%20paradigm%20is%20the%20portfolio%20operations%20pro.%20Instead%20of%20just%20minding%20companies%20between%20their%20purchase%20and%20eventual%20sale%2C%20they're%20now%20helping%20transform%20them%20into%20revenue-generating%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20now%20surrounding%20our%20financial-minded%20quants%2C%20who%20are%20the%20historical%20engine%20of%20private%20equity%2C%20with%20really%20smart%20operators%2C%20some%20of%20who've%20done%20digital%20transformation%20at%20large-scale%20corporations%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20portfolio%20operations%20partners%20were%20former%20CEOs%20and%20CFOs%20with%20a%20demonstrated%20history%20of%20successfully%20managing%20companies.%20They've%20grown%20to%20include%20professionals%20of%20all%20major%20business%20functions%20from%20HR%20and%20marketing%20to%20procurement%2C%20and%20especially%20CTOs%20and%20those%20who%20have%20driven%20major%20digital%20transformations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDesai%20said%20this%20is%20increasing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-career-advice-best-jobs-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemand%20for%20operations%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20people%20who%20might%20have%20launched%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackstone-hires-walmart-data-exec-apply-ai-portfolio-companies-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ee-commerce%20platform%20for%20Walmart%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20run%20digital%20for%20Nike%2C%20for%20example.%20These%20people%20are%20taking%20their%20talents%20to%20private%20equity%20firms%20to%20manage%20smaller%20companies%20using%20an%20already%20proven%20playbook%20for%20technological%20transformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20adding%20value%20at%20the%20shopping%20stage%20by%20assessing%20how%20long%20a%20transformation%20might%20take%20and%20what%20it%20might%20cost.%20If%20the%20deal%20goes%20forward%2C%20they're%20the%20ones%20who%20actually%20help%20run%20the%20day-to-day%20changes%20at%20those%20companies%2C%20along%20with%20the%20management%20team%20at%20the%20companies%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20unlimited%20capital%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20sound%20like%20a%20great%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20capital-constrained%20world%2C%20we've%20got%20to%20see%20what%20is%20achievable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e5a1a4d-6d6c-48c0-836e-c9e3d860c2a7%5C%22%3ECulture%20clash%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20importance%20of%20portfolio-operations%20pros%20is%20already%20taking%20hold.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20cited%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2023%2F11%2Fprivate-equity-needs-a-new-talent-strategy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard%20Business%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20operations%20(increasing%20revenue%20and%20reducing%20costs)%20contributed%20to%2047%25%20of%20all%20private-equity%20value%20creation%20since%202010%2C%20compared%20to%20the%2025%25%20of%20value%20provided%20by%20financial%20engineering.%20This%20is%20a%20reversal%20from%20the%201980s%2C%20when%20operations%20made%20up%20only%2018%25%20of%20private-equity%20value%20creation%2C%20and%20financial%20engineering%20was%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%20half%2C%20at%2051%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Desai%20warned%2C%20the%20operations%20pro's%20rising%20status%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20potential%20conflicts%20in%20the%20deal%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20portfolio-operating%20teams%20get%20under%20the%20hood%20of%20the%20portfolio%20companies%2C%20they%20uncover%20challenges%20to%20the%20value%20creation%20agenda%20or%20perhaps%20obstacles%20not%20known%20at%20the%20time%20of%20diligence%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20can%20create%20conflict%20within%20the%20fund%3B%20deals%20teams%20and%20operating%20teams%20may%20not%20see%20eye-to-eye%20on%20how%20appropriately%20one%20can%20realize%20the%20PE%20firm's%20investment%20thesis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fportfolio-operations-jobs-rising-stars-of-private-equity-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723629605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bba634955b01c3294e2e44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fportfolio-operations-jobs-rising-stars-of-private-equity-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20private-equity%20business%20model%20is%20changing%2C%20driving%20demand%20for%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20talent.%20PwC's%20Kevin%20Desai%20explains%20the%20new%20paradigm.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22anicoll%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Nicoll)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Urban%20biking%20is%20booming%20around%20the%20world%2C%20but%20New%20York%20City%20is%20falling%20behind%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams%20and%20New%20York%20Governor%20Kathy%20Hochul%20in%20the%20Red%20Hook%20neighborhood%20of%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4ebbe5da406397bf432a8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams%20endorsed%20New%20York%20Governor%20Kathy%20Hochul's%20indefinite%20postponement%20of%20congestion%20pricing%20this%20year.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lichtenstein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENYC%20is%20far%20behind%20on%20requirements%20to%20build%20bike%20and%20bus%20lanes%2C%20among%20other%20non-car%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20comes%20after%20Gov.%20Kathy%20Hochul%20suspended%20a%20new%20toll%20on%20vehicles%20in%20Manhattan%20below%2060th%20Street.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdvocates%20stress%20the%20need%20for%20better%20bike%20infras