partment%20of%20Transportation%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20controls%20the%20streets%2C%20but%20not%20trains%20and%20buses%20%E2%80%94%20is%20behind%20on%20its%20longer-term%20plan%20to%20boost%20pedestrian%20and%20bike%20infrastructure.%20The%20city's%20five-year%20NYC%20Streets%20Plan%2C%20which%20became%20law%20in%202019%2C%20requires%20the%20city%20to%20build%20250%20miles%20of%20protected%20bike%20lanes%20by%202026%2C%20among%20other%20safe%20streets%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20this%20year%2C%20the%20city%20has%20completed%20just%202.3%20miles%20of%20protected%20lanes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.transalt.org%2Fbikelanes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20advocacy%20group%20Transportation%20Alternatives%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20year%2C%20it%20built%2038.6%20miles%20of%2050%20required%20miles%20of%20protected%20bike%20lanes%20and%20in%202022%20it%20built%2019.9%20miles%20of%20the%2030%20miles%20it%20was%20required%20to%20build.%20At%20this%20time%20last%20year%2C%20it%20had%20built%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCvH-_LFOkMP%2F%3Figsh%3DMWc3b244NDJxejk5MA%253D%253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E9.7%20miles%20of%20lanes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20DOT%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20most%20bike%20lane%20construction%20happens%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year%20because%20of%20weather%20issues%2C%20and%20it%20disputed%20the%202.3-mile%20figure.%20But%20the%20department%20didn't%20provide%20an%20estimated%20number%20of%20bike%20lane%20miles%20it%20expects%20to%20complete%20this%20year.%20DOT%20noted%20that%20it%20built%20more%20protected%20lanes%20last%20year%20%26quot%3Bthan%20every%20major%20American%20city%20combined.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20isn't%20just%20required%20by%20law%20to%20build%20bike%20lanes.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amny.com%2Fnews%2Feric-adams-seeks-the-cycling-vote-with-a-promise-for-300-miles-of-bike-lanes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecampaigned%20for%20mayor%20on%20a%20promise%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20build%20300%20miles%20of%20protected%20lanes%20in%20his%20first%20four-year%20term.%20And%20the%20funding%20for%20the%20Streets%20Plan%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20%24900%20million%20%E2%80%94%20has%20already%20been%20allocated%20to%20DOT.%20The%20Adams%20administration%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fhtml%2Fdot%2Fdownloads%2Fpdf%2Fnyc-streets-plan-update-2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efallen%20behind%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20other%20priorities%20in%20the%20Streets%20Plan%2C%20including%20building%20dedicated%20bus%20lanes%20and%20upgrading%20bus%20stops.%20Advocates%20say%20the%20slow%20pace%20of%20progress%20comes%20down%20to%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20money%20is%20there%2C%20the%20law%20is%20there%2C%20but%20the%20mayor%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Elizabeth%20Adams%2C%20interim%20director%20of%20Transportation%20Alternatives.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20really%20what's%20holding%20this%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York's%20plan%20to%20impose%20a%20new%20toll%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20congestion%20pricing%20%E2%80%94%20on%20vehicles%20that%20drive%20in%20Manhattan's%20central%20business%20district%20would%20have%20been%20a%20boon%20for%20more%20sustainable%20modes%20of%20transport.%20Fewer%20cars%20and%20trucks%20on%20the%20street%20means%20more%20space%20for%20bikers%20and%20pedestrians.%20Since%20London%20implemented%20congestion%20pricing%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20daily%20car%20trips%20have%20fallen%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-02-23%2Flondon-bike-boom-risks-becoming-a-victim-of-its-own-success%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebicycling%20trips%20have%20quadrupled%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20New%20York%20Gov.%20Kathy%20Hochul%20abruptly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2