%20Joe%20Biden's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-economy-is-bidenomics-working-policies-progress-unnoticed-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterrible%20economic%20reputation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20part%20of%20the%20administration%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20Harris%20is%20unburdened%20by%20what%20has%20been.%20A%20recent%20poll%20even%20found%20that%20Americans%20trusted%20her%20with%20handling%20the%20economy%20more%20than%20the%20Republican%20ticket%2C%20a%20surprising%20feat%20for%20a%20Democratic%20candidate.%20Kamala%20does%20not%20entirely%20exist%20in%20the%20context%20that%20came%20before%20her.%20She%20looks%20around%2C%20laughs%2C%20and%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20vibecession%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20being%20a%20little%20hyperbolic%20here%2C%20but%20it%20really%20is%20the%20case%20that%20Harris%20has%20a%20serious%20opportunity%20to%20reshape%20her%20economic%20narrative.%20People%20may%20not%20be%20sold%20on%20her%20solving%20all%20their%20money%20woes%2C%20but%20enough%20voters%20appear%20willing%20to%20consider%20the%20idea%20that%20she%20might%20be%20better%20for%20their%20pocketbooks%20than%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20conventional%20wisdom%20on%20elections%20%E2%80%94%20as%20epitomized%20by%20Bill%20Clinton's%20strategist%20Jim%20Carville%20during%20Clinton's%20campaign%20in%201992%20%E2%80%94%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20economy%2C%20stupid.%26quot%3B%20It's%20an%20accurate%20sentiment%3B%20the%20economy%20typically%20ranks%20at%20or%20near%20the%20top%20of%20voters'%20most%20pressing%20issues.%20But%20it's%20also%20more%20complicated%20than%20meets%20the%20eye.%20When%20people%20say%20they're%20concerned%20about%20%26quot%3Bthe%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20can%20mean%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20%E2%80%94%20grocery%20prices%2C%20gas%20prices%2C%20housing%20prices%2C%20healthcare.%20This%20year%2C%20for%20some%20peopl