20while%2041%25%20picked%20Trump.%20Not%20everything%20in%20the%20poll%20was%20roses%20for%20Harris%20%E2%80%94%20Trump%20still%20has%20an%20edge%20on%20trade%20issues%20with%20China%20and%20who%20people%20believe%20will%20leave%20them%20better%20off%20financially%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20results%20are%20a%20marked%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHarris%20is%20being%20judged%20remarkably%20independent%20of%20the%20Biden-Harris%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Celinda%20Lake%2C%20a%20Democratic%20pollster%20and%20the%20president%20of%20Lake%20Research%20Partners.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20blaming%20Biden%20a%20lot%20as%20kind%20of%20the%20man%20in%20charge.%20But%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20new%20leaf%20now%2C%20and%20people%20are%20interested%20in%20future-forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20it%20is%20only%20one%20poll%2C%20the%20trust%20that%20Americans%20are%20putting%20in%20Harris%20is%20relatively%20unique%20for%20a%20Democrat.%20Historically%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F511979%2Fneither-party-liked-gop-holds-advantage-issues.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoters%20have%20tended%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20perceive%20Republicans%20as%20better%20stewards%20of%20the%20economy.%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F07%2F15%2Fus%2Felections%2Fbiden-vs-trump.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edid%20edge%20ahead%20of%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20some%20polls%20in%202020%20as%20the%20pandemic%20caused%20unprecedented%20economic%20chaos%2C%20but%20as%20a%20general%20rule%2C%20the%20American%20people%20think%20the%20GOP%20will%20do%20better%20on%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20the%20candidate%20is%20a%20businessman%2C%20like%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Harris%20has%20managed%20to%20upend%20the%20narrative.%20A%20late-July%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint2024.com%2Fpolling%2Fharris-july-topline%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoll%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Blueprint%2C%20a%20Democratic%20polling%20firm%2C%20found%20that%20Harris%20and%20Trump%20were%20tied%20on%20who%20voters%20trusted%20more%20to%20bring%20down%20prices%20and%20create%20jobs%20for%20everyone%20who%20needs%20one.%20Harris%20has%20an%20edge%20on%20keeping%20rent%20and%20housing%20costs%20affordable%20but%20trails%20Trump%20on%20lowering%20gas%20prices%20and%20interest%20rates.%20Blueprint%20also%20found%20Harris%20did%20much%20better%20than%20Biden%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20economic%20measures%2C%20including%20passing%20economic%20policies%20that%20people%20thought%20would%20benefit%20them%20and%20getting%20prices%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20relationship%20to%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20the%20economic%20policies%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration%20are%20not%20strongly%20associated%20with%20Kamala%20Harris%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20voters%2C%26quot%3B%20Evan%20Roth%20Smith%2C%20the%20lead%20pollster%20at%20Blueprint%2C%20said.%20On%20balance%2C%20Smith%20told%20me%2C%20voters%20are%20in%20wait-and-see%20mode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVoters%20instinctively%20are%20ready%20to%20give%20her%20a%20chance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20trust%20her%20to%20at%20least%20be%20as%20good%20as%20Trump%20on%20most%20of%20these%20economic%20things%20they%20care%20about%2C%20but%20she%20does%20have%20to%20help%20voters%20connect%20the%20dots%20on%20what%20she%20thinks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20change%20in%20perception%20is%20not%20because%20the%20economy%20transformed%20overnight%20%E2%80%94%20alas%2C%20we%20have%20not%20erased%20the%20past%20few%20years%20of%20inflation%20and%20reverted%20to%202019%20prices.%20It's%20because%20people's%20impressions%20and%20outlooks%20are%20different.%20With%20Biden%20out%20of%20the%20race%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20voters%20simply%20feel%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20elections%20are%20about%20vibes%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20Eli%20Yokley%2C%20a%20US%20policy%20analyst%20at%20Morning%20Consult%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you're%20a%20voter%2C%20and%20you%20think%20the%20vibes%20are%20bad%20%E2%80%94%20be%20it%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20be%20it%20because%20of%20the%20former%20Democratic%20presumptive%20nominee's%20age%20weighing%20on%20your%20thoughts%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20these%20things%20sort%20of%20build%20on%20themselves%20and%20shift%20perceptions%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20issues.%20We%20saw%20sentiment%20declining%20about%20Biden's%20handling%20of%20climate%20change%20or%20LGBT%20rights%2C%20the%20No.%201%20things%20where%20Democrats%20always%20are%20ahead%2C%20and%20it%20was%20moving%20at%20a%20similar%20pace%20about%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfo.civicscience.com%2Feconomic-sentiment-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Penta-CivicScience%20Economic%20Sentiment%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20measures%20Americans'%20expectations%20of%20the%20economy%20moving%20forward%2C%20saw%20a%20big%20jump%20in%20the%20last%20two%20weeks%20of%20July%2C%20about%20the%20time%20Biden%20dropped%20out%20and%20Harris%20stepped%20in.%20When%20the%20vibes%20start%20shifting%2C%20they%20shift%20on%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20people%20feel%20it%2C%20much%20of%20the%20economy%20is%20good%20on%20paper.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-second-quarter-2024-us-economy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEconomic%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20strong.%20Inflation%20is%20coming%20down%2C%20even%20if%20prices%20remain%20elevated.%20Gas%20prices%20are%20lower.%20Wages%20are%20up.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20falling.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20likely%20to%20slash%20interest%20rates%20in%20September%2C%20which%20will%20be%20a%20welcome%20relief%20to%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20alike.%20The%20labor%20market%20has%20remained%20resilient%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-labor-market-hiring-layoffs-quits-recession-sahm-rule-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethough%20some%20cracks%20are%20starting%20to%20show%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Over%20time%2C%20inflation%20should%20start%20to%20sting%20less%20as%20people%20get%20used%20to%20prices%20and%20pay%20catches%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20still%20up%20in%20arms%20about%20how%20much%20they're%20paying%20for%20things%20compared%20to%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20I%20think%20increasingly%20less%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Zandi%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Moody's%20Analytics%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Biden%20was%20limited%20in%20his%20ability%20to%20make%20this%20case.%20Democrats%20can't%20reason%20or%20argue%20or%20scream%20their%20way%20to%20convincing%20people%20the%20economy%20is%20good%20or%20getting%20them%20less%20riled%20up%20about%20the%20very%20real%20annoyance%20that%20is%20high%20prices.%20But%20maybe%2C%20with%20Harris%20as%20the%20nominee%20and%20Gov.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-vice-president-tim-walz-career-facts-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETim%20Walz%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Minnesota%20beside%20her%2C%20they%20won't%20have%20to%2C%20at%20least%20not%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20that%20voters%20think%20Harris%2C%20as%20vice%20president%2C%20has%20had%20much%20involvement%20in%20Biden's%20economic%20policies.%20A%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpro.morningconsult.com%2Fanalysis%2Fswing-state-polling-trump-harris-july-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eswing-state%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Morning%20Consult%20asked%20voters%20what%20impact%20they%20thought%20Harris%20had%20on%20the%20economy%20and%20inflation%20in%20the%20Biden%20administration.%20About%20one-third%20said%20she%20had%20a%20positive%20impact%2C%20one-third%20said%20she%20had%20a%20negative%20impact%2C%20and%20one-third%20said%20she%20had%20no%20impact%20at%20all%20or%20they%20didn't%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVoters%20don't%20quite%20know%20exactly%20how%20to%20blame%20her%20or%20how%20to%20fit%20her%20into%20that%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20Yokley%20said.%20%26quot%3BJust%20like%20her%20favorability%20numbers%20that%20we've%20seen%20improvements%20on%2C%20she%20starts%20with%20a%20much%20blanker%20slate%20than%20folks%20might%20expect%20the%20sitting%20vice%20president%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20blank%20slate%20can%20be%20used%20as%20an%20advantage.%20Harris%20can%20talk%20about%20a%20distinct%20vision%20and%20more-popular%20policies%2C%20whether%20it%20be%20tackling%20housing%20costs%20or%20supporting%20wealth%20building%20or%20fostering%20entrepreneurship%20or%20creating%20jobs%20or%20supporting%20the%20middle%20class.%20And%20she%20doesn't%20have%20to%20utter%20the%20words%20%26quot%3Binflation%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BBidenomics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20has%20an%20opening%20because%20people%20are%20like%2C%20'OK%2C%20let's%20take%20a%20new%20look%2C'%26quot%3B%20Lake%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20race%20to%20define%20what%20her%20economic%20perspective%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20this%20opportunity%2C%20Harris%20does%20have%20to%20compete%20with%20some%20history.%20There's%20a%20deep%20partisan%20divide%20in%20the%20way%20people%20say%20they%20feel%20about%20the%20economy.%20When%20a%20Democrat%20is%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Democratic%20voters%20say%20everything%20is%20awesome%2C%20and%20Republicans%20say%20everything%20is%20terrible.%20When%20a%20Republican%20gets%20elected%2C%20it%20flips.%20As%20mentioned%2C%20voters%20often%20trust%20Republicans%20over%20Democrats%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20many%20polls%20indicate%20Trump%20still%20has%20an%20advantage%20over%20Harris.%20People%20remember%20the%20Trump%20economy%20as%20a%20better%20time%20%E2%80%94%20interest%20rates%20were%20lower%2C%20prices%20were%20lower%2C%20houses%20seemed%20more%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20people%20don't%20even%20know%20what%20the%20policies%20are%2C%20but%20they%20sure%20know%20how%20much%20their%20groceries%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20Whit%20Ayres%2C%20a%20Republican%20pollster%20and%20political%20consultant%2C%20said.%20Still%2C%20that's%20one%20factor%20of%20many.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20say%20that%20inflation%20is%20more%20important%20than%20Donald%20Trump's%20character%20or%20inflation%20is%20more%20important%20than%20Kamala%20Harris'%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20apples%20and%20oranges.%20It's%20two%20different%20sets%20of%20concerns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20task%20for%20Harris%20now%20is%20to%20lay%20out%20an%20economic%20identity%20and%20agenda%20before%20others%20beat%20her%20to%20it.%20She%20ran%20on%20a%20quite%20progressive%20agenda%20in%20the%202020%20Democratic%20presidential%20primaries%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2024%2F08%2F09%2Fkamala-harris-pivots-progressive-policies-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe's%20shifted%20some%20of%20her%20positions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20clear%20to%20what%20extent%20that's%20much%20of%20a%20guidepost%20for%20what%20she'd%20do%20as%20POTUS.%20In%20the%20Senate%20representing%20California%2C%20Harris%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2018%2F10%2Flefts-trump-sized-tax-plans%2F573328%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20tax%20credits%20to%20lower-%20and%20middle-income%20families.%20On%20the%202024%20campaign%20trail%2C%20she's%20also%20likely%20to%20tout%20her%20prosecutorial%20record%20as%20California's%20attorney%20general%20in%20going%20after%20pharmaceutical%20companies%20and%20big%20banks%2C%20including%20securing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fworld%2Fkamala-harris-stood-up-to-big-banks-with-mixed-results-for-consumers-in-crisis-idUSKCN1SF0Z4%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2420%20billion%20settlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20financial%20institutions%20during%20the%20foreclosure%20crisis.%20At%20a%20rally%20in%20Las%20Vegas%20early%20this%20month%2C%20Harris%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F08%2F12%2Fpolitics%2Ftaxes-on-tips-eliminate-proposal-harris%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20would%20fight%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-labor-market-federal-minimum-wage-raise-small-business-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraising%20the%20minimum%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20endorsed%20eliminating%20taxes%20on%20tips%20for%20service%20workers.%20The%20latter%20is%20a%20proposal%20Trump%20has%20already%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20likely%20does%20have%20to%20put%20forward%20a%20positive%20message%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20though%20given%20the%20excitement%20around%20her%2C%20she%20may%20not%20want%20to%20get%20too%20in%20the%20weeds%20on%20it.%20She%20could%20also%20probably%20make%20some%20hits%20on%20Trump.%20He's%20proposing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftrump-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuite%20of%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20many%20economists%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariff-trade-policy-barrier-income-tax-rate-hikes-krugman-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20increase%20prices%20even%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20would%20push%20to%20extend%20the%202017%20tax%20cuts%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tax-plan-rich-people-benefits-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisproportionately%20benefit%20the%20wealthy%3C%