quot%3Bskipping%20stone%26quot%3B%20technique%20that%20sees%20the%20missile%20bounce%20off%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20China%20does%20manage%20to%20further%20the%20range%20of%20its%20missiles%2C%20it%20can%20strike%20far%20deeper%20into%20US%20territory.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20scientists%20in%20China%20believe%20they've%20found%20a%20way%20to%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-and-russia-have-deployed-hypersonic-missiles-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehypersonic%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20potent%20%E2%80%94%20by%20extending%20their%20range%20via%20%26quot%3Bskipping%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20from%20the%20China%20Aerodynamics%20Research%20and%20Development%20Center%20say%20the%20method%20would%20involve%20a%20hypersonic%20glide%20vehicle%20repeatedly%20boosting%20upward%20and%20then%20falling%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20as%20it%20travels%20to%20its%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technique%20is%20called%20skip-gliding%2C%20where%20the%20vehicle%20flies%20to%20the%20edge%20of%20space%20and%20then%20bounces%20off%20the%20denser%20upper%20layers%20of%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20like%20a%20stone%20skipping%20on%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20potentially%20increase%20the%20range%20of%20a%20hypersonic%20missile%20by%20up%20to%2034%25%20and%20its%20flight%20time%20by%2028%25%2C%20according%20to%20their%20simulations%2C%20which%20were%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yhxb.org.cn%2FthesisDetails%2310.3873%2Fj.issn.1000-1328.2024.06.008%26amp%3Blang%3Dzh%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeer-reviewed%20Journal%20of%20Astronautics'%20June%20issue.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fscience%2Farticle%2F3273658%2Fchinas-new-hypersonic-glider-can-power-jump-other-side-earth-scientists%3Fmodule%3Dtop_story%26pgtype%3Dhomepage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHong%20Kong-based%20South%20China%20Morning%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20on%20their%20research%20on%20Thursday%2C%20writing%20that%20it%20could%20herald%20the%20use%20of%20hypersonic%20missiles%20moving%20from%20%26quot%3Bregional%20conflict%20to%20global%20operation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20scientists%2C%20led%20by%20principal%20author%20Yong%20Enmi%2C%20said%20their%20work%20was%20inspired%20in%20part%20by%20the%20Silbervogel%20space%20plane%20envisioned%20by%20aerospace%20engineers%20under%20Nazi%20Germany%20and%20the%20US%20Air%20Force's%20Dyna-Soar%20project%20in%20the%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20planes%20were%20designed%20to%20cover%20vast%20distances%20at%20high%20speeds%20using%20skip-gliding%2C%20but%20neither%20was%20ever%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYong's%20team%20said%20that%20their%20computer%20simulations%20showed%20China's%20hypersonic%20missiles%20could%20travel%20at%20speeds%20of%20up%20to%20Mach%2020%20and%2C%20after%20an%20hour%20of%20flight%2C%20still%20maintain%20a%20velocity%20of%20Mach%207%20as%20they%20skip%20on%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-hypersonic-weapon-fired-something-off-during-flight-report-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMost%20hypersonic%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20understood%20to%20follow%20a%20far%20different%20flight%20trajectory.%20They're%20typically%20launched%20high%20into%20the%20sky%2C%20sometimes%20to%20low%20space%2C%20and%20glide%20toward%20their%20target%20before%20re-entering%20the%20atmosphere%20to%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20China%20tested%20a%20version%20that%20could%20circumnavigate%20the%20globe%20in%202021%2C%20the%20US%20was%20stunned.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-hypersonic-missile-surprised-us-spies-with-its-space-capability-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20appeared%20to%20have%20been%20caught%20off%20guard%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20how%20quickly%20Beijing%20had%20developed%20the%20technology%2C%20and%20worried%20that%20it%20would%20spell%20trouble%20for%20missile%20defense%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20full%20Chinese%20hypersonic%20arsenal%20with%20an%20extended%20range%20would%20have%20serious%20military%20implications%2C%20Jennifer%20Kavanagh%2C%20director%20of%20Military%20Analysis%20at%20Washington-based%20think%20tank%20Defense%20Priorities%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20mean%20that%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20can%20launch%20these%20weapons%20from%20far%20inside%20China%20and%20still%20strike%20deep%20into%20American%20territory%2C%20potentially%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20or%20even%20Hawaii%20or%20the%20US%20mainland%2C%20Kavanagh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20easier%20for%20the%20PLA%20to%20protect%20%E2%80%94%20and%20harder%20for%20the%20United%20States%20to%20find%20and%20target%20%E2%80%94%20missile%20systems%20based%20deep%20inside%20China%20than%20those%20that%20must%20be%20positioned%20along%20the%20coast%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkip-gliding%20missiles%20may%20also%20be%20harder%20to%20track%20and%20intercept%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20research%20only%20involved%20simulations%20and%20not%20actual%20missile%20tests%2C%20Kavanagh%20said.%20Even%20if%20China%20were%20able%20to%20translate%20this%20into%20a%20practical%20weapon%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20be%20expensive%20and%20complicated%20to%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheory%20and%20practice%20can%20be%20very%20different%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20missile%20ranges%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kavanagh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHypersonic%20missiles%20are%20especially%20difficult%20to%20maneuver%20as%20they%20get%20faster%2C%20and%20they%20tend%20to%20heat%20up%20quickly%20at%20top%20speeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKavanagh%20noted%20that%20a%20future%20skip-gliding%20missile%20would%20likely%20still%20be%20detectab