ng%20a%20real%20campaign%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20that%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.natesilver.net%2Fp%2Fof-course-bidens-age-is-a-legitimate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Ehis%20age%20was%20dragging%20down%20his%20chances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20and%20that%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.natesilver.net%2Fp%2Fits-time-for-the-white-house-to-put%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDemocrats%20should%20have%20swapped%20him%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20you%20worry%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20you%20got%20all%20of%20that%20wrong%3F%20That%20people%20would%20be%20as%20upset%20with%20you%20as%20they%20were%20after%20the%202016%20campaign%2C%20when%20you%20said%20Hilary%20Clinton%20was%20heavily%20favored%20to%20beat%20Trump%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20I%20thought%20people%20were%20in%20denial%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20Trump%20actually%20had%20a%20decent%20chance%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20only%20a%20couple%20of%20points%20down%20in%20these%20critical%20states%2C%20and%20Clinton%20had%20all%20types%20of%20signs%20of%20weaknesses.%20So%20then%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20emphasize%20that%20Trump%20did%20have%20a%20shot%2C%20and%20%5Bthe%20fact%20that%20people%20didn't%20understand%20that%5D%20was%20frustrating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20I%20was%20even%20more%20skeptical%20about%20Biden%20than%20the%20polls.%20He%20was%20down%20to%2C%20like%2C%20a%2026%25%20chance%20in%20our%20model%2C%20but%20that%20assumes%20that%20he's%20running%20a%20normal%20campaign%20and%20not%20trying%20to%20avoid%20media%20appearances%2C%20and%20not%20having%20all%20his%20fundraising%20dry%20up%20and%20things%20like%20that.%20And%20so%20I%20thought%20his%20real%20chance%20might%20have%20been%2010%25%20or%2015%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20poker%20player%2C%20it's%20kind%20of%20like%20getting%20