f%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-antitrust-doj-ruling-monopoly-search-apple-iphone-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremedies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20How%20will%20the%20US%20government%20decide%20to%20fix%20this%20monopoly%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20one%20potential%20remedy%20that%20a%20few%20smart%20investors%20are%20whispering%20about.%20One%20hedge%20fund%20analyst%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20confidential%20research%20note.%20It's%20also%20really%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20that%20the%20US%20would%20require%20Google%20to%20make%20its%20Search%20index%20publicly%20available%20for%20anyone%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8fbb2a8-770a-4725-a335-dade93caa2fc%5C%22%3EBots%20and%20indexes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Search%20index%20is%20created%20by%20a%20bot%20crawling%20the%20web%20and%20collecting%20keywords%20and%20other%20information%20from%20sites.%20Google%20then%20stores%20all%20that%20in%20a%20database.%20When%20you%20type%20a%20query%20into%20Google's%20Search%20engine%2C%20the%20company's%20technology%20zips%20through%20this%20index%20to%20find%20matching%20and%20similar%20keywords%2C%20which%20are%20tied%20back%20to%20the%20relevant%20websites.%20Then%20Google%20shows%20you%20the%20most%20relevant%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20bit%20like%20how%20you%20find%20a%20topic%20in%20a%20big%20book%20by%20looking%20it%20up%20in%20the%20index%20at%20the%20back%2C%20rather%20than%20reading%20the%20whole%20book%20every%20time%20you%20need%20a%20specific%20bit%20of%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20Search%20index%20is%20the%20biggest%20in%20the%20world.%20Without%20it%2C%20the%20company's%20search%20engine%20wouldn't%20work%20very%20well%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERivals%20have%20tried%20to%20build%20alternative%20Search%20indexes%20for%20decades.%20It's%20really%20hard%2C%20partly%20because%20websites%20don't%20like%20lots%20of%20random%20bots%20crawling%20all%20over%20their%20content.%20Sites%20often%20block%20these%20other%20bots.%20But%20they%20can't%20block%20Google's%20because%20the%20company's%20Search%20dominance%20means%20that%20sites%20would%20lose%20massive%20traffic%20if%20they%20did%20that.%20You%20can%20see%20this%20in%20action%20today%20with%20several%20top%20websites%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseveral-top-news-sites-shun-openai-searchgpt-search-engine-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblocking%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E's%20new%20Search%20bot%2C%20but%20not%20Google's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20Google's%20dominant%20index%20an%20open%20public%20resource%20would%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20in%20a%20dramatic%20way%20because%20rivals%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20build%20their%20own%20indexes%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c2ffd122-50ec-4f6b-a8c1-2256c4408d0b%5C%22%3EThe%20Search%20index%20as%20part%20of%20the%20public%20commons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWouldn't%20this%20be%20taking%20something%20that%20belongs%20to%20Google%2C%20though%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20really.%20The%20Search%20index%20is%20a%20collection%20of%20keywords%20and%20other%20data%20from%20websites%20that%20have%20been%20created%20by%20other%20people%20and%20other%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20not%20Google.%20Google%20doesn't%20own%20this%20stuff.%20Instead%2C%20it%20makes%20everyone%20else's%20content%20available%20through%20its%20Search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it's%20not%20too%20much%20of%20a%20stretch%20to%20require%20that%20Google%20make%20the%20index%20part%20of%20the%20public%20commons%2C%20that%20set%20of%20cultural%20and%20natural%20resources%20shared%20by%20everyone%20for%20the%20good%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20mission%20statement%20is%20%26quot%3Bto%20organize%20the%20world's%20information%20and%20make%20it%20universally%20accessible%20and%20useful.%26quot%3B%20What%20better%20way%20to%20make%20this%20more%20accessible%20than%20by%20sharing%20this%20index%20of%20the%20world's%20information%20without%20restraint%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7b82371-e80b-4c9b-b11d-452e77e80306%5C%22%3EAn%20open%20index%20could%20spark%20new%20Search%20approaches%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20happened%2C%20I%20could%20imagine%20hundreds%20of%20new%20search%20products%20taking%20different%2C%20inventive%20ways%20to%20fetch%2C%20rank%2C%20and%20present%20all%20the%20information%20lurking%20in%20this%20huge%20index%20of%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Amit%20Mehta's%20monopoly%20decision%20identified%20Google's%20data%20advantage%20as%20a%20big%20reason%20alternative%20products%20like%20Microsoft's%20Bing%20are%20sometimes%20lower%20quality.%20So%2C%20creating%20a%20more%20competitive%20environment%20would%20require%20more%20equality%20in%20data.%20In%20the%20same%20way%20Bing%20powers%20DuckDuckGo%2C%20Google's%20open%20index%20could%20power%20other%20rival%20search%20engines%20that%20could%20offer%20different%20approaches%20to%20Google's%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff65893a-052d-4b89-978d-47e32d6126ca%5C%22%3EAn%20API%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20be%20done%20through%20an%20open%20API%2C%20or%20application%20programming%20interface%2C%20which%20lets%20different%20applications%20communicate%20and%20share%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20could%20charge%20money%20for%20giving%20index%20access%20to%20large%20commercial%20players%2C%20while%20providing%20the%20index%20free%20to%20researchers%20and%20other%20smaller%20organizations%2C%20along%20with%20maybe%20a%20low%20price%20for%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228b750daf-4cfd-43fd-a1b6-23ace7222266%5C%22%3EAn%20MVNO%20analogy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20analogy%20of%20how%20this%20can%20work%20is%20from%20the%20wireless%20industry.%20Mobile%20Virtual%20Network%20Operators%2C%20or%20MVNOs%2C%20offer%20cellular%20service%20for%20your%20smartphone.%20But%20they%20don't%20own%20their%20own%20network%20of%20cell%20towers%20and%20other%20expensive%20equ