The%20boycott%20gained%20traction%2C%20especially%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%20such%20as%20TikTok%20and%20X%2C%20where%20the%20hashtag%20%23boycottstarbucks%20had%20millions%20of%20views.%C2%A0Many%20continue%20to%20say%20that%20Starbucks%20is%20either%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20supporting%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20more%20to%20it.%20Starbucks%20is%20an%20American%20company%2C%20and%20the%20US%20has%20been%20a%20staunch%20ally%20of%20Israel%2C%20providing%20substantial%20military%20aid%20and%20diplomatic%20support%20for%20their%2010-month-long%20military%20campaign%20in%20Gaza.%20Since%20October%207%2C%20in%20what%20Israel%20has%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bretaliatory%26quot%3B%20action%2C%20nearly%20all%20schools%20and%20hospitals%20have%20been%20targeted%20and%20scores%20of%20tent%20camps%20have%20been%20bombed%20killing%20thousands%20--%20a%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20children%20and%20women.%20The%20roughly%20360%20square%20km%C2%A0area%20of%20Gaza%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20rubble.%20At%20least%201.9%20million%20people%20have%20been%20displaced%20internally%2C%20with%20many%20forced%20to%20move%20nine%20to%20ten%20times%20during%20the%20course%20of%20this%20war.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnProgressive%20groups%20in%20the%20US%20and%20abroad%20are%20increasingly%20vocal%20about%20their%20opposition%20to%20Israeli%20policies%2C%20fuelling%20the%20boycotts%20of%20American%20companies%20perceived%20to%20be%20pro-Israel.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStarbucks'%20stance%20on%20the%20Israeli%20genocide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20has%20firmly%20denied%20claims%20of%20supporting%20Israel%20or%20any%20other%20government%20or%20military%20operation%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20In%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20coffee%20giant%20said%20they%20%26quot%3Bcondemned%20violence%26quot%3B%20and%20stressed%20their%20commitment%20to%20providing%20a%20welcoming%20and%20inclusive%20environment%20for%20all%20customers%20worldwide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStarbucks%20is%20a%20global%20company%20committed%20to%20providing%20a%20place%20where%20everyone%20feels%20welcome%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging%2C%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%20Our%20hearts%20break%20for%20all%20affected%20by%20the%20violence%20and%20conflict%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20We've%20always%20condemned%20violence%20against%20the%20innocent%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstories.starbucks.com%2Fpress%2F2023%2Fwhat-has-starbucks-said-about-the-conflict-in-israel-and-gaza%2F%C2%A0%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20reiterated%20that%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Bnever%20contributed%20to%20any%20government%20or%20military%20operation%26quot%3B%2C%20but%20the%20damage%20was%20done%2C%20and%20the%20brand%20continues%20to%20face%20backlash%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20In%20response%20to%20declining%20sales%2C%20Starbucks'%20Middle%20East%20franchises%20had%20to%20fire%202%2C000%20employees%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20brands%20facing%20calls%20for%20boycott%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20facing%20these%20challenges.%20Other%20global%20brands%20have%20also%20been%20targeted%20for%20boycotts%20due%20to%20perceived%20or%20real%20connections%20with%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFast%20food%20giant%20McDonalds%20was%20boycotted%20due%20to%20its%20support%20for%20Israel.%20The%20controversy%20began%20when%20Omri%20Padan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20McDonald's%20Israeli%20franchise%2C%20offered%20free%20meals%20to%20Israeli%20forces.%20This%20gesture%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20show%20of%20support%20for%20the%20Israeli%20military%2C%20sparking%20calls%20for%20a%20boycott.%20The%20boycott%20gained%20momentum%20in%20other%20countries%20such%20as%20Kuwait%2C%20Malaysia%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20where%20consumers%20accused%20McDonald's%20of%20having%20a%20pro-Israel%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisney%2B%20has%20faced%20boycotts%20due%20to%20its%20perceived%20support%20of%20Israel%2C%20with%20activists%20calling%20for%20a%20boycott%20of%20the%20platform.%20Clothing%20brand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fzara-pulls-out-controversial-ad-amid-boycott-calls-4658825%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPeople%2520on%2520X%2520(formerly%2520Twitter%2Cat%2520mass%2520graves%2520in%2520Gaza.%C2%A0%5C%22%3EZara%20was%20boycotted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0after%20its%20marketing%20campaign%20featured%20rubble%20and%20body%20bags%2C%20leading%20to%20protests%20outside%20stores%20in%20several%20countries.%20Critics%20called%20the%20campaign%20%26quot%3Btone-deaf%26quot%3B%2C%20forcing%20the%20clothing%20brand%20to%20pull%20it%20down%20from%20all%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPuma%20has%20been%20targeted%20by%20boycotts%20due%20to%20its%20sponsorship%20of%20the%20Israeli%20Football%20Association.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20fast-food%20chains%20have%20also%20faced%20boycotts%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20due%20to%20their%20perceived%20support%20of%20Israel.%20Domino's%2C%20Pizza%20Hut%2C%20and%20KFC%20have%20all%20faced%20challenges%20in%20the%20region%2C%20while%20Burger%20King%20has%20faced%20boycotts%20in%20Turkey%20due%20to%20its%20perceived%20support%20of%20Israel.%20Coca-Cola%2C%20too%2C%20has%20faced%20similar%20boycotts%20in%20Turkey%20and%20parts%20of%20South%20Asia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723624260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fgll77q1o_starbucks_625x300_15_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-why-starbucks-is-being-boycotted-6334266%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Starbucks%20has%20come%20under%20fire%20for%20its%20alleged%20connection%20with%20Israel.%20The%20calls%20for%20a%20boycott%20intensified%2C%20especially%20after%20Israel's%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza%20killed%20nearly%2040%2C000%20Palestinians%20and%20left%20about%20100%2C000%20injured.%22%