tps%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fallcargo-logistics-q1-results-net-profit-down-97-at-rs-3-36-crore-124081400744_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Income%20from%20operations%20for%20the%20quarter%20under%20review%2C%20however%2C%20rose%2046%20per%20cent%20year-on-year%20to%20Rs%20526.47%20crore%20from%20Rs%20360.26%20crore%20in%20Q1%20FY24%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fallcargo-logistics-q1-results-net-profit-down-97-at-rs-3-36-crore-124081400744_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fallcargo-logistics-q1-results-net-profit-down-97-at-rs-3-36-crore-124081400744_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fallcargo-logistics-q1-results-net-profit-down-97-at-rs-3-36-crore-124081400744_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rajnath%20Singh%20Chairs%20Key%20Security%20Meet%20Over%20Rising%20Terror%20Attacks%20In%20J%26amp%3BK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDefence%20Minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20convened%20a%20high-level%20meeting%20today%20focusing%20on%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20terror-related%20incidents%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20meeting%2C%20held%20at%20the%20South%20Block%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20was%20attended%20by%20top%20officials%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20(NSA)%20Ajit%20Doval%20and%20Army%20Chief%20General%20Upendra%20Dwivedi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20was%20called%20in%20response%20to%20a%20series%20of%20terror-related%20incidents%20that%20have%20plagued%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%20recent%20months.%20The%20security%20forces%20across%20the%20Union%20Territory%20have%20been%20placed%20on%20high%20alert%20ahead%20of%20Independence%20Day.%20An%20Army%20captain%20was%20killed%20and%20four%20terrorists%20were%20gunned%20down%20in%20an%20ongoing%20operation%20in%20the%20higher%20reaches%20of%20Jammu's%20Doda%20district%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20Jammu%20has%20become%20increasingly%20volatile%2C%20with%20a%20noticeable%20uptick%20in%20terror%20attacks.%20On%20August%2010%2C%20two%20soldiers%20and%20a%20civilian%20were%20killed%20during%20a%20gunfight%20between%20terrorists%20and%20security%20forces%20in%20Anantnag.%20The%20region%20has%20witnessed%20attacks%20on%20an%20army%20convoy%20in%20Kathua%2C%20skirmishes%20in%20Doda%20and%20Udhampur%2C%20and%20a%20failed%20attack%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20Border%20Action%20Team%20(BAT)%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LoC)%20in%20Kupwara%20district's%20Machchal%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%2C%2028%20people%2C%20including%20civilians%20and%20security%20personnel%2C%20were%20killed%20in%2011%20terror-related%20incidents%20and%2024%20counter-terror%20operations%20up%20to%20July%2021%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20two%20months%2C%20the%20frequency%20of%20attacks%20and%20ambushes%20has%20increased%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20southern%20reaches%20of%20Pir%20Panjal%2C%20an%20area%20that%20had%20been%20relatively%20quiet%20in%20terms%20of%20terrorist%20activity%20for%20some%20time.%20Notable%20among%20recent%20incidents%20was%20an%20operation%20in%20which%20two%20Army%20officers%20were%20killed%2C%20and%20two%20Pakistani%20terrorists%2C%20including%20a%20Lashkar-e-Taiba%20sniper%20and%20explosives%20expert%2C%20were%20eliminated.%20Overall%2C%20casualties%20among%20security%20forces%20have%20doubled%20this%20year%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20three%20years%2C%20with%2017%20security%20personnel%20and%20an%20equal%20number%20of%20civilians%20losing%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20official%20told%20NDTV%20that%20the%20increased%20military%20casualties%20are%20a%20significant%20concern%2C%20which%20has%20led%20to%20the%20rationalisation%20of%20force%20deployment%20in%20the%20area%20with%20new%20combinations%20and%20strategies.%20The%20government%2C%20while%20maintaining%20a%20focus%20on%20securing%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%2C%20has%20also%20recognised%20the%20need%20to%20bolster%20security%20in%20the%20Jammu%20region.%20This%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20mobilisation%20of%20additional%20forces%20for%20deployment%20in%20key%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20primary%20objectives%20of%20the%20government's%20new%20security%20strategy%20is%20to%20plug%20infiltration%20routes%20used%20by%20terrorists%20to%20enter%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Security%20audits%20conducted%20by%20various%20agencies%20have%20identified%20around%20two%20dozen%20sectors%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LoC)%20in%20the%20Valley%20and%20the%20International%20Border%20in%20the%20Jammu%20sector%20where%20infiltration%20has%20been%20recorded.%20Terrorists%2C%20often%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20local%20guides%2C%20use%20these%20routes%20to%20cross%20into%20Indian%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20infiltration%20by%20foot%2C%20there%20is%20also%20evidence%20of%20weapons%20being%20smuggled%20across%20the%20border%20or%20dropped%20via%20drones.%20To%20counter%20this%2C%20the%20government%20has%20initiated%20a%20project%20to%20fence%20the%20borders.%20However%2C%20progress%20has%20been%20slow%2C%20with%20only%2070%20out%20of%20180%20kilometres%20of%20the%20border%20in%20Jammu%20having%20been%20fenced%20so%20far%2C%20and%20floodlighting%20completed%20for%20only%2040%20kilometres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20battalions%20of%20the%20Border%20Security%20Force%20(BSF)%2C%20comprising%202%2C000%20personnel%2C%20have%20been%20airlifted%20from%20Odisha%20and%20deployed%20in%20the%20Samba%20sector%20to%20plug%20gaps%20along%20the%20Jammu-Punjab%20border.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecent%20intelligence%20reports%20suggest%20that%20terrorists%20may%20target%20highways%2C%20which%20are%20vital%20for%20troop%20movements%20and%20logistics.%20To%20secure%20these%20%26quot%3Blifelines%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20government%20has%20decided%20to%20deploy%20CRPF%20personnel%20along%20with%20local%20police%20to%20patrol%20highways%20and%20adjacent%20areas.%20Drones%20are%20also%20being%20used%20to%20monitor%20and%20map%20these%20areas%20for%20any%20suspicious%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723623660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-08%2Fijh7pb8o_jammu-and-kashmir-army-pti_625x300_05_August_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajnath-singh-chairs-key-security-meet-over-rising-terror-attacks-in-j-k-6334916%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Defence%20Minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20convened%20a%20high-level%20meeting%20today%20focusing%20on%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20terror-related%20incidents%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajnath-singh-chairs-key-security-meet-over-rising-terror-attacks-in-j-k-6334916%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20did%20Japan's%20PM%20Kishida%20resign%3A%20A%20visionary%20step%20or%20compulsion%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723623235000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-112518049%2Cimgsize-679822.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fwhy-did-japans-pm-kishida-resign-a-visionary-step-or-compulsion%2Farticleshow%2F112518011.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F112518011.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EJapanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%20announced%20he%20will%20not%20seek%20re-election%20in%20the%20September%20LDP%20leadership%20vote.%20Kishida's%20popularity%20had%20dipped%20